The eThekwini city manager, Sipho Nzuza, was arrested this morning and appeared in the Durban Commercial Crimes Court today (Tuesday, 10 March). He was granted bail of R50 000 and will appear in court with other co-accused on 16 April. He is one of several officials who have been accused in the R389 million Durban Solid Waste (DSW) tender fraud case. Amongst the accused are former mayor, Zandile Gumede, DSW deputy head Robert Abbu, and other municipal officials who were arrested last year. The eThekwini Municipality has appealed to the media and others to be given space to process the matter internally. They said that they will issue a statement during the course of the week. The municipality spokesperson, Msawakhe Mayisela said: “As a government institution, the municipality will always co-operate with law enforcement agencies and give them space to do their work.” Mayisela has assured residents that service delivery will not be affected.